{"key":"post-11517293","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11517293</id>\n<content>With oysters, they'll look and taste better if he can find a place in the garage or an outdoor shed to fruit them at lower than ambient room temperature.&amp;nbsp; Room temp is great for colonization, but oysters will grow meatier and have better quality if fruited in 55F to 60F temperature with lots of fresh air and bright light.&amp;nbsp; A shotgun terrarium will be fine if fanned out daily a few times, but as said, find a cool place to set it.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For his second grow, spawn the brf cakes to straw for much more yield.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11517306</next>\n<prev>11517271</prev>\n<first>11516010</first>\n<last>11517892</last>\n<when>1259077603</when>\n<utime>11/24/09 05:46 PM</utime>\n</post>"}